<DOC><DOCNO> AP890215-0104 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-15-89 1248EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--MaskedPolice     02-15 0073</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Masked Police,0074</SECOND><HEAD>Traffic Police Don Masks in Protest</HEAD><DATELINE>FLORENCE, Italy (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Traffic police donned surgical masksWednesday and mounted a protest demanding heavier fines for driverswho violate anti-pollution rules.   Traffic officials said the officers believe the fine of about $9is too low to discourage private motorists from driving into thecongested historic center without authorization.   Pollution blamed mainly on car exhaust is plaguing Florence andother Italian cities.</TEXT></DOC>